n.md` | Session routing design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/spec.md` | Redis/Valkey session store spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/design.md` | Session store design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Idle cleanup controller (agentd) spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/idle-cleanup/design.md` | Idle cleanup design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/spec.md` | Python SDK spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md` | Python SDK design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md` | Helm chart, Docker, Makefile build targets spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` | Deployment design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/client-go.md` | Generated client-go library documentation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/spec.md` | Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer integration spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md` | Integrations design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/spec.md` | CI/CD pipeline spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/design.md` | CI/CD design |\n\n#### AR (Acceptance Requirements) Change Directories:\n\nLocated in workspace changes directories (33 ARs total, AR-001 through AR-033):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-001/` through `AR-033/`\n- Each AR directory contains: `design.md`, `proposal.md`, `tasks.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\nExample AR files:\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-001/design.md` -- CRD AgentRuntime type definition\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-005/design.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/design.md`\n\n#### AR Log Files (benchmark results):\nLocated under `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/*/` -- hundreds of `AR-XXX_ST-N.log` files tracking benchmark task execution.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Test Files\n\nAll test files are in the Python SDK:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | AgentRuntimeClient tests (179 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` | CodeInterpreterClient tests (234 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient tests (217 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests (335 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests (198 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py` | Utility function tests (119 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy tests (104 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/pytest.ini` | Pytest configuration |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Build Targets (from Makefile)\n\nThe Makefile at `/home/dsj/benchmark/Makefile` defines these targets:\n\n| Target | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `help` | Show available targets |\n| `setup` | Install Python dependencies (`pip install -r requirements.txt`) |\n| `preflight` | Verify environment (`TOOL`, `MODEL`) |\n| `proxy` | Start LiteLLM Proxy on configurable port |\n| `run-v51` | Run benchmark: `TOOL=xxx MODEL=xxx [ORIG_REPO=path] [AR_LIMIT=N]` |\n| `run-v51-proxy` | Run benchmark through LiteLLM Proxy |\n| `run-v51-dry` | Dry run (test prompts, no API calls) |\n| `batch-v51` | Run all tool x model combinations |\n| `batch-v51-proxy` | Run all combos through LiteLLM Proxy |\n| `report-v51` | Generate report from latest run |\n| `compare-v51` | Generate cross-run comparison report |\n| `export-v51` | Export v5.1 runs to CSV/JSON/Markdown |\n| `mock` | Generate mock data report |\n| `selftest` | Validate latest data against schema |\n| `clean-v51` | Remove v5.1 workspaces, results, and reports |\n| `clean` | Remove all generated results |\n\n**Note:** The deployment spec (`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md`) references additional Makefile targets in the upstream AgentCube Go repository (not this benchmark repo): `build`, `test`, `docker-*`, `generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`, `e2e`, `e2e-clean`, `lint`, `gen-copyright`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Project Summary\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. This benchmark repository (`/home/dsj/benchmark`) is an **SDD-TEE (Spec-Driven Development Token Efficiency Evaluation)** framework that:\n\n1. **Reads detailed specs** from `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/` -- covering sandbox orchestration, code execution (PicoD), session routing, session storage, CLI toolkit, Python SDK, deployment, CI/CD, idle cleanup, and integrations.\n2. **Feeds specs to AI coding agents** (Claude Code, OpenCode CLI, Gemini CLI, Cursor, etc.) paired with various models.\n3. **Tracks implementation** through 33 Acceptance Requirements (AR-001 through AR-033), each with design docs, proposals, task lists, and delta specs.\n4. **Measures token efficiency** across 7-stage implementation (ST-0 through ST-7).\n5. **Generates reports** comparing different tool/model combinations.\n\nThe Python SDK (`sdk-python/`) provides client libraries for interacting with AgentCube's control plane (Workload Manager) and data plane (Router/PicoD).\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2856e3fd9ffeUIEtQOJODN4tvc","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775877865507,"end":1775878012789}}}}
