{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878018025,"sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a94127a0010J3NLmYCNBSRqO","messageID":"msg_d7a93ffbf001HBW22tftyg2xJw","sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e83b97d95c3c40de86b485b8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SDD-TEE: SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation\n2: # CodeSpec 7-Stage × OpenSpec OPSX\n3: #\n4: # Usage:\n5: #   make run-v51 TOOL=claude-code MODEL=claude-sonnet-4\n6: #   make run-v51-proxy TOOL=gemini-cli MODEL=gemini-3.1-pro\n7: #   make batch-v51                           # all combos\n8: #   make dry-v51 TOOL=claude-code MODEL=claude-sonnet-4  # test prompts\n9: \n10: TOOL     ?= claude-code\n11: MODEL    ?= claude-sonnet-4\n12: SPECS    := specs\n13: RESULTS  := results\n14: RUNS     := $(RESULTS)/runs\n15: REPORTS  := $(RESULTS)/reports\n16: PROXY_PORT ?= 4000\n17: ORIG_REPO ?=\n18: \n19: .PHONY: help setup preflight proxy \\\n20:         run-v51 run-v51-proxy run-v51-dry \\\n21:         batch-v51 batch-v51-proxy \\\n22:         report-v51 compare-v51 export-v51 \\\n23:         clean-v51 clean selftest mock\n24: \n25: # --- Environment ---\n26: setup:  ## Install Python dependencies\n27: \tpip install -r requirements.txt\n28: \n29: preflight:  ## Verify environment\n30: \tpython3 scripts/preflight.py --tool $(TOOL) --model $(MODEL)\n31: \n32: # --- LiteLLM Proxy ---\n33: proxy:  ## Start LiteLLM Proxy\n34: \tlitellm --config configs/litellm_config.yaml --port $(PROXY_PORT)\n35: \n36: # --- v5.1 Benchmark ---\n37: run-v51:  ## Run benchmark: TOOL=xxx MODEL=xxx [ORIG_REPO=path] [AR_LIMIT=N]\n38: \tbash scripts/run_benchmark.sh $(TOOL) $(MODEL) $(if $(AR_LIMIT),--ar-limit $(AR_LIMIT),) $(if $(ORIG_REPO),--original-repo $(ORIG_REPO),)\n39: \n40: run-v51-proxy:  ## Run benchmark through LiteLLM Proxy\n41: \tbash scripts/run_benchmark.sh $(TOOL) $(MODEL) --api-base http://localhost:$(PROXY_PORT) $(if $(ORIG_REPO),--original-repo $(ORIG_REPO),)\n42: \n43: run-v51-dry:  ## Dry run (test prompts, no API calls)\n44: \tbash scripts/run_benchmark.sh $(TOOL) $(MODEL) --dry-run-prompts\n45: \n46: batch-v51:  ## Run all tool×model combinations\n47: \tbash scripts/batch_benchmark.sh\n48: \n49: batch-v51-proxy:  ## Run all combos through LiteLLM Proxy\n50: \tbash scripts/batch_benchmark.sh --api-base http://localhost:$(PROXY_PORT)\n51: \n52: # --- Reporting ---\n53: report-v51:  ## Generate report from latest run\n54: \t@FULL_JSON=$$(ls -t $(RUNS)/v5.1/*_full.json 2>/dev/null | head -1); \\\n55: \tif [ -n \"$$FULL_JSON\" ]; then \\\n56: \t\tpython3 scripts/report.py --data \"$$FULL_JSON\" 2>/dev/null || true; \\\n57: \t\techo \"Report: $(REPORTS)/v5.1/\"; \\\n58: \telse \\\n59: \t\techo \"No v5.1 data found. Run 'make run-v51' first.\"; \\\n60: \tfi\n61: \n62: compare-v51:  ## Generate cross-run comparison report\n63: \t@RUN_COUNT=$$(ls $(RUNS)/v5.1/*_full.json 2>/dev/null | wc -l); \\\n64: \tif [ \"$$RUN_COUNT\" -gt 0 ]; then \\\n65: \t\tmkdir -p $(REPORTS)/v5.1; \\\n66: \t\tpython3 scripts/compare.py \\\n67: \t\t\t--runs $(RUNS)/v5.1/*_full.json \\\n68: \t\t\t--output $(REPORTS)/v5.1/compare_report.html; \\\n69: \t\techo \"Report: $(REPORTS)/v5.1/compare_report.html\"; \\\n70: \telse \\\n71: \t\techo \"No v5.1 runs found.\"; \\\n72: \tfi\n73: \n74: export-v51:  ## Export v5.1 runs to CSV/JSON/Markdown\n75: \tpython3 scripts/export.py --format all --output $(REPORTS)/v5.1\n76: \n77: # --- Testing ---\n78: mock:  ## Generate mock data report\n79: \tpython3 scripts/report.py --mock\n80: \n81: selftest:  ## Validate latest data against schema\n82: \t@FULL_JSON=$$(ls -t $(RUNS)/v5.1/*_full.json 2>/dev/null | head -1); \\\n83: \tif [ -n \"$$FULL_JSON\" ]; then \\\n84: \t\tpython3 scripts/schema.py \"$$FULL_JSON\"; \\\n85: \telse \\\n86: \t\techo \"No data found. Run 'make mock' or 'make run-v51' first.\"; \\\n87: \tfi\n88: \n89: # --- Maintenance ---\n90: clean-v51:\n91: \trm -rf workspaces/v5.1/* results/runs/v5.1/* $(REPORTS)/v5.1/*\n92: \n93: clean:  ## Remove all generated results\n94: \trm -rf $(RUNS)/v5.1/* $(REPORTS)/v5.1/* workspaces/v5.1/*\n95: \n96: help:  ## Show this help\n97: \t@grep -E '^[a-zA-Z_-]+:.*?## ' $(MAKEFILE_LIST) | sort | awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*?## \"}; {printf \"  \\033[36m%-22s\\033[0m %s\\n\", $$1, $$2}'\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SDD-TEE: SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation\n# CodeSpec 7-Stage × OpenSpec OPSX\n#\n# Usage:\n#   make run-v51 TOOL=claude-code MODEL=claude-sonnet-4\n#   make run-v51-proxy TOOL=gemini-cli MODEL=gemini-3.1-pro\n#   make batch-v51                           # all combos\n#   make dry-v51 TOOL=claude-code MODEL=claude-sonnet-4  # test prompts\n\nTOOL     ?= claude-code\nMODEL    ?= claude-sonnet-4\nSPECS    := specs\nRESULTS  := results\nRUNS     := $(RESULTS)/runs\nREPORTS  := $(RESULTS)/reports\nPROXY_PORT ?= 4000\nORIG_REPO ?=\n\n.PHONY: help setup preflight proxy \\\n        run-v51 run-v51-proxy run-v51-dry \\","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"Makefile","time":{"start":1775878018016,"end":1775878018023}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878018671,"sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9414bb0016bIalOHhtaxDeQ","messageID":"msg_d7a93ffbf001HBW22tftyg2xJw","sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aab2d269d9804fff8c6c9b7d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775878018663,"end":1775878018669}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775878018750,"sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9416b10010wm2W94jthgf6z","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a93ffbf001HBW22tftyg2xJw","sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19107,"input":18883,"output":143,"reasoning":81,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.005581532}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878020019,"sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a941bb00015gmmp5M1nHp4rR","messageID":"msg_d7a9416d3001XUyg96Zoa1uU0J","sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878021716,"sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a941d85001LmF6i8nfCUJ4wl","messageID":"msg_d7a9416d3001XUyg96Zoa1uU0J","sessionID":"ses_2856e5babffeZWduG7T80RJqfm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_65809b16c1604f3a924d2058","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `root`\n6: - **Language:** Makefile\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the creation of a root-level `Makefile` for the AgentCube project, providing a unified entry point for building Go binaries, Docker images, running tests, linting, and Helm operations. The Makefile SHALL orchestrate existing tooling (go, docker, helm, golangci-lint) without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Variables and Configuration\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Default variable values\n19: The Makefile SHALL define the following variables with default values that can be overridden by the caller:\n20: \n21: | Variable | Default | Description |\n22: |----------|---------|-------------|\n23: | `TAG` | `latest` | Docker image tag |\n24: | `REGISTRY` | `agentcube` | Docker image registry prefix |\n25: | `GOOS` | `$(shell go env GOOS)` | Target operating system |\n26: | `GOARCH` | `$(shell go env GOARCH)` | Target architecture |\n27: | `BIN_DIR` | `bin` | Binary output directory |\n28: | `LDFLAGS` | `-s -w` | Linker flags (strip debug + compress) |\n29: | `VERBOSE` | (empty) | Set to `1` to enable verbose command output |\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: TAG override\n32: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker TAG=v0.1.0`\n33: - **WHEN** Docker images are built\n34: - **THEN** the image tag SHALL be `v0.1.0` instead of `latest`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: REGISTRY override\n37: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker REGISTRY=myregistry.io/agentcube`\n38: - **WHEN** Docker images are built\n39: - **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `myregistry.io/agentcube/`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Cross-compilation via GOOS/GOARCH\n42: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64`\n43: - **WHEN** Go binaries are compiled\n44: - **THEN** `GOOS=linux` and `GOARCH=arm64` SHALL be passed to `go build`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: VERBOSE enables command echo\n47: - **GIVEN** `VERBOSE=1` is set\n48: - **WHEN** any target executes\n49: - **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL be printed before execution\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: VERBOSE=0 suppresses command echo\n52: - **GIVEN** `VERBOSE` is not set or is empty\n53: - **WHEN** any target executes\n54: - **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL NOT be printed (silent by default)\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Go Build Targets\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: build\n61: The Makefile SHALL provide a `build` target that compiles all Go binaries to `$(BIN_DIR)/`. The binaries SHALL be: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: build compiles all binaries\n64: - **GIVEN** the project root contains `cmd/router/`, `cmd/workloadmanager/`, `cmd/agentd/`, `cmd/picod/`\n65: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n66: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router`, `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, and `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist as executable files\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: build uses LDFLAGS\n69: - **GIVEN** `LDFLAGS` is set to `-s -w`\n70: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n71: - **THEN** `go build` SHALL be invoked with `-ldflags '-s -w'`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: build applies GOOS/GOARCH\n74: - **GIVEN** `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64` is executed\n75: - **WHEN** the binaries are compiled\n76: - **THEN** all output binaries SHALL be built for `linux/amd64`\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: build/<binary>\n79: The Makefile SHALL provide per-binary build targets in the form `build/<binary>` for each of: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: build/router compiles only router\n82: - **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n83: - **WHEN** the build completes\n84: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router` SHALL exist\n85: - **AND** `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL NOT be created by this invocation\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: build/picod compiles only picod\n88: - **GIVEN** `make build/picod` is executed\n89: - **WHEN** the build completes\n90: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: build/<binary> uses correct package path\n93: - **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n94: - **WHEN** the build command is inspected\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` (not `./cmd/` or any other path)\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: clean\n98: The Makefile SHALL provide a `clean` target that removes the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory and all build artifacts.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: clean removes bin directory\n101: - **GIVEN** `make build` has been run and `$(BIN_DIR)/` exists with binaries\n102: - **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n103: - **THEN** the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory SHALL be removed\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: clean is idempotent\n106: - **GIVEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/` does not exist\n107: - **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n108: - **THEN** the command SHALL succeed without error\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Docker Build Targets\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: docker\n115: The Makefile SHALL provide a `docker` target that builds all Docker images: `agentcube` (from `docker/Dockerfile`), `router` (from `docker/Dockerfile.router`), and `picod` (from `docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: docker builds all images\n118: - **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=latest REGISTRY=agentcube` is executed\n119: - **WHEN** the build completes\n120: - **THEN** the following images SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon:\n121:   - `agentcube/agentcube:latest`\n122:   - `agentcube/router:latest`\n123:   - `agentcube/picod:latest`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: docker uses correct Dockerfiles\n126: - **GIVEN** `make docker` is executed\n127: - **WHEN** the docker build commands are inspected\n128: - **THEN** the agentcube image SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile`, router SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.router`, and picod SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: docker applies TAG variable\n131: - **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=v0.2.0` is executed\n132: - **WHEN** the build completes\n133: - **THEN** all images SHALL be tagged with `v0.2.0` (e.g., `agentcube/agentcube:v0.2.0`)\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: docker applies REGISTRY variable\n136: - **GIVEN** `make docker REGISTRY=ghcr.io/myorg` is executed\n137: - **WHEN** the build completes\n138: - **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `ghcr.io/myorg/` (e.g., `ghcr.io/myorg/router:latest`)\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: docker/<image>\n141: The Makefile SHALL provide per-image build targets in the form `docker/<image>` for each of: `agentcube`, `router`, `picod`.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: docker/router builds only router image\n144: - **GIVEN** `make docker/router TAG=latest` is executed\n145: - **WHEN** the build completes\n146: - **THEN** `agentcube/router:latest` SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n147: - **AND** `agentcube/agentcube:latest` and `agentcube/picod:latest` SHALL NOT be built by this invocation\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: docker/picod uses correct Dockerfile\n150: - **GIVEN** `make docker/picod` is executed\n151: - **WHEN** the docker build command is inspected\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod` with the project root as build context\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Test Targets\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: test\n159: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test` target that runs all Go unit tests.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: test runs all Go tests\n162: - **GIVEN** `make test` is executed\n163: - **WHEN** the command completes\n164: - **THEN** `go test ./...` SHALL have been executed\n165: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect test pass/fail (non-zero on failure)\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: test-coverage\n168: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test-coverage` target that runs Go tests with coverage profiling and writes the output to `coverage.out`.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: test-coverage generates coverage report\n171: - **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n172: - **WHEN** the command completes\n173: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n174: - **AND** the file SHALL contain valid Go coverage data (parseable by `go tool cover`)\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: test-coverage covers all packages\n177: - **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n178: - **WHEN** the command is inspected\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL include `-coverprofile=coverage.out` flag\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: test-chart\n182: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test-chart` target that runs the Helm chart render test script.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: test-chart executes render script\n185: - **GIVEN** `make test-chart` is executed\n186: - **WHEN** the command completes\n187: - **THEN** `bash test/chart/test_render.sh` SHALL have been executed\n188: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect the script's pass/fail status\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ## Code Quality Targets\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: lint\n195: The Makefile SHALL provide a `lint` target that runs `golangci-lint`.\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: lint runs golangci-lint\n198: - **GIVEN** `make lint` is executed\n199: - **WHEN** the command completes\n200: - **THEN** `golangci-lint run` SHALL have been executed\n201: - **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint violations are found\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: fmt\n204: The Makefile SHALL provide a `fmt` target that formats Go source code.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: fmt formats all Go files\n207: - **GIVEN** `make fmt` is executed\n208: - **WHEN** the command completes\n209: - **THEN** `go fmt ./...` SHALL have been executed\n210: - **AND** any unformatted Go files SHALL be reformatted in place\n211: \n212: ### Requirement: vet\n213: The Makefile SHALL provide a `vet` target that runs Go's static analyzer.\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: vet runs go vet\n216: - **GIVEN** `make vet` is executed\n217: - **WHEN** the command completes\n218: - **THEN** `go vet ./...` SHALL have been executed\n219: - **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if vet issues are found\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Helm Targets\n224: \n225: ### Requirement: helm-lint\n226: The Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-lint` target that validates Helm charts.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: helm-lint validates charts\n229: - **GIVEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n230: - **WHEN** the command completes\n231: - **THEN** `helm lint manifests/` (or the appropriate chart path) SHALL have been executed\n232: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect lint pass/fail\n233: \n234: ### Requirement: helm-template\n235: The Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-template` target that renders Helm templates for inspection.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: helm-template outputs rendered manifests\n238: - **GIVEN** `make helm-template` is executed\n239: - **WHEN** the command completes\n240: - **THEN** `helm template` SHALL output the rendered Kubernetes manifests to stdout\n241: - **AND** the command SHALL NOT modify any files (read-only operation)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Python Targets\n246: \n247: ### Requirement: python-lint\n248: The Makefile SHALL provide a `python-lint` target that runs Python linting tools against the SDK/CLI code, gracefully handling the case where tools are not installed.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: python-lint runs ruff when available\n251: - **GIVEN** `ruff` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n252: - **WHEN** the command completes\n253: - **THEN** `ruff check` (or equivalent) SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI source\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: python-lint succeeds when tools are absent\n256: - **GIVEN** neither `ruff` nor `flake8` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n257: - **WHEN** the command completes\n258: - **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating no lint tool was found\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: python-test\n261: The Makefile SHALL provide a `python-test` target that runs Python tests, gracefully handling the case where pytest is not installed.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: python-test runs pytest when available\n264: - **GIVEN** `pytest` is installed and `make python-test` is executed\n265: - **WHEN** the command completes\n266: - **THEN** `pytest` SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI test directory\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: python-test succeeds when pytest is absent\n269: - **GIVEN** `pytest` is not installed and `make python-test` is executed\n270: - **WHEN** the command completes\n271: - **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating pytest was not found\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Composite Targets\n276: \n277: ### Requirement: all\n278: The Makefile SHALL provide an `all` target that serves as the default target and runs a complete local development verification.\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: all runs build, test, and lint\n281: - **GIVEN** `make` (or `make all`) is executed with no arguments\n282: - **WHEN** the command completes\n283: - **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, and `make lint` SHALL all have been executed\n284: - **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure (non-zero exit code)\n285: \n286: ### Requirement: ci\n287: The Makefile SHALL provide a `ci` target that runs the full CI gate verification suite.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: ci runs full CI gate\n290: - **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n291: - **WHEN** the command completes\n292: - **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, `make test-coverage`, `make lint`, and `make helm-lint` SHALL all have been executed\n293: - **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: ci produces coverage output\n296: - **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n297: - **WHEN** the command completes successfully\n298: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## Phony Targets\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: .PHONY declaration\n305: All non-file-producing targets SHALL be declared as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: all targets are phony\n308: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is parsed\n309: - **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n310: - **THEN** the following targets SHALL be declared `.PHONY`:\n311:   `all`, `build`, `clean`, `test`, `test-coverage`, `test-chart`, `lint`, `fmt`, `vet`,\n312:   `docker`, `helm-lint`, `helm-template`, `python-lint`, `python-test`, `ci`,\n313:   and all `build/<binary>` and `docker/<image>` targets\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: phony targets work even if同名 files exist\n316: - **GIVEN** a file named `build` exists in the project root\n317: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n318: - **THEN** the Makefile target SHALL execute (not treat `build` as a file dependency)\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Error Handling\n323: \n324: ### Requirement: Build failure propagation\n325: When any sub-command in a target fails, the Makefile SHALL propagate the non-zero exit code.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: go build failure stops build\n328: - **GIVEN** a Go source file contains a compilation error\n329: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n330: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status\n331: - **AND** no further binaries SHALL be built after the failure\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: test failure stops ci\n334: - **GIVEN** a Go test is failing\n335: - **WHEN** `make ci` is executed\n336: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status after `make test` fails\n337: - **AND** `make lint` and `make helm-lint` SHALL NOT be executed\n338: \n339: ### Requirement: Missing tool graceful handling\n340: Targets that depend on external tools (golangci-lint, helm, ruff, pytest) SHALL fail with a clear error message when the tool is not found, except for Python targets which SHALL warn and succeed.\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: golangci-lint missing causes lint failure\n343: - **GIVEN** `golangci-lint` is not installed\n344: - **WHEN** `make lint` is executed\n345: - **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `golangci-lint` is required\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: helm missing causes helm-lint failure\n348: - **GIVEN** `helm` is not installed\n349: - **WHEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n350: - **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `helm` is required\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## File Changes\n355: \n356: | Action | File | Description |\n357: |--------|------|-------------|\n358: | Create | `Makefile` | Root-level Makefile with all build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets |\n\n(End of file - total 358 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `root`\n- **Language:** Makefile\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of a root-level `Makefile` for the AgentCube project, providing a unified entry point for building Go binaries, Docker images, running tests, linting, and Helm operations. The Makefile SHALL orchestrate existing tooling (go, docker, helm, golangci-lint) without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Variables and Configuration\n\n### Requirement: Default variable values\nThe Makefile SHALL define the following variables with default values that can be overridden by the caller:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878021707,"end":1775878021714}}}}
